  <tr valign="top" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
    <td height="164" colspan="2" class="normalFont"><p>I enjoy playing the guitar and making music. I also like to write music-related software. Feel free to visit the links below.</p>
      <p><strong>Guitar Instruction:</strong></p>
      <ul>
      	<li><a
	  href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~asuncion/GuitarFactory/GIG/gig.htm">Guitar Intelli-Generator (G.I.G.)</a>: This applet is perhaps the most versatile guitar chord applet on the Internet. This program actually generates all the possible positions of a desired chord. There is support for full and partial capos as well as alternate tunings. Best of all, it's free to use!</li>
        <li><a
href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~asuncion/GuitarFactory/start.htm">Guitar Factory</a>: I made this site when I was doing guitar tutoring. To play the guitar, you really only have to know two things: 1) the chords; 2) the strumming/picking patterns. The Guitar Factory will teach you how to strum and pick simple patterns. G.I.G. will teach you the chords. </li>

      </ul>
	  <p><strong>Music:</strong></p>
	  <ul>
	    <li><strong>Grace Again</strong>  [ <a href="music/GraceAgain.mp3">mp3 (4 MB)</a> ]: This is a mellow guitar instrumental that I made a while ago. It is in the alternate tuning of GCEGCD. The reason for the title is because I tried to emulate a similar guitar piece called "Grace" by Danny Donnelly, and because the ending cadence is the melody of "Amazing Grace."
	    <li><strong>So Amazed </strong> [ <a href="music/SoAmazed.mp3">mp3 (5.2 MB)</a> ] [ <a href="music/SoAmazed.txt">chord sheet</a> ]: This song took a while to record. It is about a love that never ceases to amaze me.
      </li>
      </ul>
	  <p class="footer"> <em>Copyright &copy; 2004-2007 Arthur Asuncion. Downloading any music from this site signifies that you have agreed to use the music only for noncommercial personal use.</em></p>
